Package: countmissingvalues
Type: Package
Title: count_all_missing_by_group
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Linoja Sajanthan <lino.sajanthan@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Linoja Sajanthan <lino.sajanthan@gmail.com>
Description: This package provides a function, `count_all_missing_by_group`, which 
    calculates the number of missing (NA) values for all columns in a dataset,
    grouped by a specific column. It is designed to handle data frames or tibbles 
    and can be used for missing data analysis in grouped data. The function returns 
    a summary of missing values by group, making it easier to identify where data 
    might be missing across different levels of the grouping column.
